<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D" The regular icosahedron, often si=
mply called &quot;the&quot; icosahedron, is the regular polyhedron and Plat=
onic solid illustrated above having 12 polyhedron vertices, 30 polyhedron e=
dges, and 20 equivalent equilateral triangle faces, 20{3}. It is illustrate=
d above together with a wireframe version and a net that can be used for it=
s construction. The regular icosahedron is also the uniform polyhedron with=
 Maeder index 22 (Maeder 1997), Wenninger index 4 (Wenninger 1989), Coxeter=
 index 25...">
