m/images/equations/RegularIcosahedron/Inline4.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" =
style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"14" height=
=3D"21" alt=3D"I_h"> of symmetries. The connectivity of
 the vertices is given by the <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Icos=
ahedralGraph.html">icosahedral graph</a>.
</p>
<div class=3D"center-image">
<img style=3D"max-width:100%;max-height:100%;" width=3D"912.96" src=3D"http=
s://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/eps-svg/IcosahedronConvexHulls_1000.svg" c=
lass=3D"" alt=3D"IcosahedronConvexHulls">
</div>
<p>
The regular icosahedron is the <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Con=
vexHull.html">convex hull</a> of the first and second <a href=3D"https://ma=
thworld.wolfram.com/DodecahedronStellations.html">dodecahedron stellations<=
/a>,
