" height=3D"27" alt=3D" V=3D20[(1/3A)r]=3D5/(12)(3+sqrt(5))a^3. "></td><td =
align=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn22" class=3D"eqnum">
(22)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
Apollonius showed that for an icosahedron and a <a href=3D"https://mathworl=
d.wolfram.com/Dodecahedron.html">dodecahedron</a>
with the same <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Inradius.html">inrad=
ius</a>,
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
<tbody><tr><td align=3D"left"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/RegularIcosahedron/NumberedEquation15.svg" class=3D"numberede=
quation" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"196=
" height=3D"42" alt=3D" (V_(icosahedron))/(V_(dodecahedron))=3D(A_(icosahed=
ron))/(A_(dodecahedron)), "></td><td align=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn23" class=3D"eqnum">
(23)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
where <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/RegularIco=
sahedron/Inline61.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max=
-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"13" height=3D"21" alt=3D"V">
 is the volume and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equatio=
ns/RegularIcosahedron/Inline62.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-he=
ight:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"12" height=3D"21" alt=3D"A"=
>
 the <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SurfaceArea.html">surface are=
a</a>, with the actual ratio being
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
<tbody><tr><td align=3D"left"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/RegularIcosahedron/NumberedEquation16.svg" class=3D"numberede=
quation" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"320=
" height=3D"42" alt=3D" (V_(icosahedron))/(V_(dodecahedron))=3D(A_(icosahed=
ron))/(A_(dodecahedron))=3Dsqrt(3/(10)(5-sqrt(5))). "></td><td align=3D"rig=
ht" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn24" class=3D"eqnum">
(24)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
